<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
A single male belonging this species was collected in 
<number box="[751,807,1287,1311]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="2014.0">2014</number>
flying about five meters from the ground around 
<number box="[1358,1385,1286,1311]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="13.0">13</number>
:00h in the same place and time where males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Seitz, 1913" authorityName="Seitz" authorityYear="1913" box="[634,975,1322,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Alesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rothschildi">
<emphasis box="[634,823,1322,1347]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Alesa rothschildi</emphasis>
(Seitz, 
<number box="[909,966,1323,1347]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1913.0">1913</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
were found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
This species was described from Bogotá, 
<collectingCountry box="[680,790,1358,1383]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Colombia</collectingCountry>
based on a male and a female deposited at the 
<collectionCode box="[1345,1433,1359,1382]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">BMNH</collectionCode>
. Apparently the record from 
<collectionCode box="[463,534,1395,1419]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
is the second for this species and the first one for 
<collectingCountry box="[1089,1161,1394,1419]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. As suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number box="[267,325,1430,1455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName box="[341,460,1430,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[341,460,1430,1455]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably close ally to 
<taxonomicName authority="Talbot, 1929" authorityName="Talbot" authorityYear="1929" box="[748,1032,1430,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Alesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sticheli">
<emphasis box="[748,861,1430,1455]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. sticheli</emphasis>
(Talbot, 
<number box="[964,1024,1431,1455]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1929.0">1929</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a species only known from 
<collectingCountry name="French Guiana" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[248,502,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott 
<number box="[443,502,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" box="[514,822,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard 
<number box="[762,822,1466,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In fact the specimen found in 
<collectionCode box="[1182,1254,1467,1491]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
has a upperside pattern of both wings similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[514,632,1502,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[514,632,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whereas the aspect of the blue spots of both wings underside is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[185,303,1538,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Alesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sticheli">
<emphasis box="[185,303,1538,1563]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. sticheli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on these differences, it would be possible that the specimen from 
<collectionCode box="[1199,1271,1539,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
represents an undescribed taxon, however, considering that the male genitalia remains unknown for both 
<taxonomicName box="[1226,1349,1574,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[1226,1349,1574,1599]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Alesa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sticheli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. sticheli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the description of the specimen from 
<collectionCode box="[657,729,1611,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
as new would be inadvisable.
</paragraph>
